            </div>
                <div style="clear:both;"></div></aside>
            <!-- Share buttons by mashshare.net - Version: 3.8.1--></div><footer class="entry-footer"><p class="entry-meta"><span class="entry-categories">Categories: <a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/category/sucuri-updates" rel="category tag">Sucuri Updates</a>, <a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/category/website-security" rel="category tag">Website Security</a></span><span class="entry-tags">Tags: <a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/tag/industry-reports" rel="tag">Industry Reports</a>, <a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/tag/ossec" rel="tag">OSSEC</a>, <a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/tag/server-security" rel="tag">Server Security</a>, <a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/tag/website-monitoring" rel="tag">Website Monitoring</a></span></p></footer></article><section class="author-box"><img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/df3ec5506ba59d2ed3b951b7057e97d0?s=115&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/df3ec5506ba59d2ed3b951b7057e97d0?s=230&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-115 photo' height='115' width='115' loading='lazy'/><h4 class="author-box-title">About <span itemprop="name">Daniel Cid</span></h4><div class="author-box-content" itemprop="description"><p>Daniel B. Cid is Founder of Sucuri and the VP of Engineering for the  GoDaddy Security Products group. He is also the founder of OSSEC and <a href="https://cleanbrowsing.org">CleanBrowsing</a>.  You can find more about Daniel on his site <a href="http://dcid.me">dcid.me</a> or on <a href="https://twitter.com/danielcid">Twitter: @danielcid</a></p>
